#: ../../../variable/CTEST_PRESET.rst:2
msgid "CTEST_PRESET"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_PRESET.rst:6
msgid ""
"Specify a preset name to use for all relevant :manual:`ctest(1)` :ref:"
"`Dashboard Client` steps in a dashboard script, or on the :program:`ctest` "
"command line via the :ctest-dashboard-option:`-D` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_PRESET.rst:10
msgid ""
"This variable sets the ``PRESET`` option for :command:`ctest_configure`, :"
"command:`ctest_build`, :command:`ctest_test`, and :command:`ctest_memcheck` "
"when those commands are not given an explicit ``PRESET`` argument and the "
"corresponding command-specific variable (:variable:"
"`CTEST_CONFIGURE_PRESET`, :variable:`CTEST_BUILD_PRESET`, or :variable:"
"`CTEST_TEST_PRESET`) is also unset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_PRESET.rst:17
msgid ""
"For :command:`ctest_configure`, an error is raised if no configure preset "
"with this name exists.  For :command:`ctest_build`, :command:`ctest_test`, "
"and :command:`ctest_memcheck`, a warning is emitted and the variable is "
"ignored if no preset of the matching type exists with this name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_PRESET.rst:22
msgid "See also :variable:`CTEST_PRESETS_FILE`."
msgstr ""
